title: Are You Paying Too Much for Electricity? | National LED Energy Broker
description:
Want to know what you’re really being billed every month for electricity?
National LED’s new Energy Broker Services help businesses uncover hidden fees, negotiate better rates, and lower their energy costs. We break down your supplier charges, delivery fees, and demand charges so you finally know your true cost per kWh—and then we go to work to reduce it.

Pair that with our proven LED lighting solutions, and you’re saving on both usage and supply.

⚡ The National LED Advantage

Here’s why businesses trust us to handle both lighting and energy:

✅ All-In Transparent Quotes – True “all-in” rates, factoring in supplier, TDSP, and estimated taxes.
✅ Fair, Competitive Fees – No hidden markups. We negotiate directly with providers so you pay less.
✅ Ongoing Bill Management – We monitor bills, manage renewals, and catch overcharges.
✅ Lighting + Energy Expertise – LED upgrades cut usage, while our brokerage lowers supply rates.
✅ Scalable Solutions – Multi-location or relocating? We handle setup, transfers, and consolidation.

📩 Ready to see if you’re overpaying? Send us your latest bill today and let’s start saving.

title: Cut Your Lighting Bill in Half!
description:
What Cost Savings Can I Expect With LED Lighting? | Customer Q&A

In this episode of our Q&A series, a National LED sales rep breaks down what kind of cost savings you can expect by switching to LED lighting.

💡 Rule of Thumb? Cut your current lighting energy use in HALF.
For example: replacing a 1000W metal halide with a 500–600W LED fixture instantly slashes energy consumption.

We also aim for a return on investment (ROI) in 5 years or less, and that’s just the beginning. As utility companies continue to raise energy rates, your savings only grow over time. Your LED wattage stays the same, but your old costs keep climbing.

✅ Lower wattage

title: What happens after you sign the proposal?
description:
Our Sales Director explains the next steps:
Once we receive your signed proposal, our accounting team will reach out for a 50% deposit. From there, we confirm that your LED fixtures are ready to go. Once everything’s in stock, we coordinate with our electricians to schedule your installation. After the job is complete, we do a final walkthrough to ensure everything looks great, and you're 100% satisfied.
